en_104575_0	Customs apprehended a stock of satellite communication equipment and long distance remote control equipment yesterday.
en_104575_1	That was at the Katunayake airport passenger terminal.
en_104575_2	Reports say that this stock of equipment was found in the traveling bag of the leader of a group returning from a pilgrimage to India.
en_104575_3	Customs media spokesman Leslie Gamini told our news team that it was illegal to import such satellite equipment without obtaining permission of the Telecommunication Regulatory Commission.
